{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9a3e6f98-d490-4552-a69f-96490dc60499","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework Support Dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- ❌ `netcoreapp3.1` — not supported (EOL)\n- ❌ `net5.0` — not supported (EOL)\n- ✅ `net462` — still supported\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for the modern .NET side and **.NET Framework 4.6.2+** for legacy.\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. **Update target frameworks** — replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with supported versions (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. **Simplify package references** — MSTest v3 consolidates into a single `MSTest` package, replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages.\n\n**Example updated `.csproj`:**\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n```\n\nAlso review your test code for any **breaking API changes** (e.g., removed `Assert` overloads, changes to `DataRow` attribute behavior, stricter initialization). The [MSTest v3 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/testing/unit-testing-mstest-migration) covers these in detail.\n\nWant me to go ahead and update the project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"754dc5ae-f76a-4184-90ef-31f2db80a87a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3. Let me think about what compatibility issues they'd face.\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Specifically:\n- MSTest v3 requires .NET Framework 4.6.2 or later (so net462 should be okay)\n- MSTest v3 dropped support for .NET Core 3.1 and .NET 5.0 — it requires .NET 6.0+ for the .NET (Core) side\n\n\n- The packages were also consolidated into a single `MSTest` meta-package instead of separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages\n\nSo the real issue here is that `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` won't be compatible with MSTest v3 at all.","outputTokens":698,"requestId":"6038:28AA9B:27FCA9F:2A74FF1:6A04945A"},"id":"fdd04a6c-f14d-4f2e-837a-ed0aa0691adb","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:10:33.066Z","parentId":"4f277439-1045-417d-a138-ca1856a32cdc"}
